<item>
            <title>[SPARK-22222] Fix the ARRAY_MAX in BufferHolder and add a test</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-22222</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is actually a followup for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-22033&quot; title=&quot;BufferHolder, other size checks should account for the specific VM array size limitations&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-22033&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-22033&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which set the `ARRAY_MAX` to `Int.MaxValue - 8`. It is not a valid number because it will cause the following line fail when such a large byte array is allocated: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/sql/catalyst/src/main/java/org/apache/spark/sql/catalyst/expressions/codegen/BufferHolder.java#L86&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/sql/catalyst/src/main/java/org/apache/spark/sql/catalyst/expressions/codegen/BufferHolder.java#L86&lt;/a&gt; We need to make sure the new length is a multiple of 8.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to add one test for the fix. Note that the test should work independently with the heap size of the test JVM. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
